description:
&lt;p&gt;The RCHT Commissioning, Performance and Intelligence (CPI) team’s role is to improve patient care through providing expert support and advice to clinical services in Cornwall.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The CPI team have an exciting new opportunity for 2 Elective Performance Officers to join the team and support a range of different areas, including leading on the management of outpatient space, maximising outpatient throughput and providing support to the Care Groups in their elective recovery plans.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer a friendly, supportive, developmental environment and the opportunity to get involved in all aspects of the function depending on the preferences and interests of the successful candidate, as well as strong broader links across the organisation and the system and consequently an environment that whilst challenging is always interesting.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a fulltime post working 37.5 hours per week, though flexible/part time working applications will be considered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Claire Florey, Deputy Associate Director – Commissioning, Performance and Intelligence, on 01872 252230 or email c.florey@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
